WEBVTT

00:04.404 --> 00:05.372 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.405 --> 00:06.373 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.406 --> 00:07.374 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:07.407 --> 00:09.243 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight:

00:09.276 --> 00:11.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, PRESIDENT OF THE
UNITED STATES:
We can choose to press forward
with a better

00:11.378 --> 00:19.086 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
model of cooperation and
integration, or we
can retreat into a world sharply
divided.

00:19.119 --> 00:24.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Obama
gives his final
speech at the U.N. General
Assembly, facing

00:24.391 --> 00:29.496 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a historic refugee crisis and
struggling cease-fire
in Syria.

00:29.529 --> 00:35.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Also ahead this
Tuesday: The CEO
of Wells Fargo apologizes for
millions of

00:35.402 --> 00:38.972 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fraudulent accounts, but says
the practice
wasn't a scheme.

00:39.006 --> 00:44.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN STUMPF, CEO, Wells Fargo &amp;
Company: We
never directed nor wanted our
team members

00:44.077 --> 00:48.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to provide products and services
to customers
that they didn't want.

00:48.515 --> 00:53.754 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And exploring the
presidential
candidates' plans on education.

00:53.787 --> 00:57.524 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We continue our series looking
at the issues
shaping the election.

00:57.557 --> 01:05.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: All that and more on
tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:05.365 --> 01:08.201 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:08.235 --> 01:17.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For the president
today, a
moment on the world stage at the
United Nations

01:17.878 --> 01:23.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
one last time, his message no
less than an
urgent plea to make a better
world.

01:23.817 --> 01:28.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
At this moment, we all face a
choice.

01:28.088 --> 01:33.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It was his final
address to
the U.N. General Assembly, and
President Obama

01:33.460 --> 01:35.629 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
used it to issue a challenge.

01:35.662 --> 01:41.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: We can choose to
press forward
with a better model of
cooperation and integration,

01:41.335 --> 01:49.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or we can retreat into a world
sharply divided
and ultimately in conflict along
age-old lines

01:49.276 --> 01:51.979 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of nation and tribe and race and
religion.

01:52.012 --> 01:58.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The president
spoke of a growing
contest between authoritarian
rule and liberalism,

01:58.151 --> 02:03.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and of people losing faith in
the face of
terrorism and the refugee
crises.

02:03.223 --> 02:07.861 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BARACK OBAMA: Given the
difficulty in forging
true democracy in the face of
these pressures,

02:07.894 --> 02:14.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's no surprise that some argue
the future
favors the strong man, a
top-down model, rather

02:14.868 --> 02:17.604 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
than strong democratic
institutions.

02:17.637 --> 02:20.107 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I believe this thinking is
wrong.

02:20.140 --> 02:24.478 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I believe the road of true
democracy remains
the better path.

02:24.511 --> 02:30.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mr. Obama
appealed to the world
to do more for the millions
fleeing war-torn

02:30.417 --> 02:32.319 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
countries.

02:32.352 --> 02:36.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he warned against the
politics of Donald
Trump, without mentioning the
Republican nominee

02:36.189 --> 02:37.958 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by name.

02:37.991 --> 02:42.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: The world is too
small for us
to simply be able to build a
wall and prevent

02:42.262 --> 02:44.231 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it from affecting our own
societies.

02:44.264 --> 02:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: The prime minister of the
United Kingdom.

02:46.833 --> 02:51.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Newly named
British Prime Minister
Theresa May, making her first
address at the

02:51.872 --> 02:57.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.N. after her country's vote to
leave the
European Union, said Brexit was
not a signal

02:57.911 --> 03:00.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that Britain was retreating from
its global
responsibilities.

03:00.981 --> 03:04.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
THERESA MAY, British Prime
Minister: They
didn't vote to turn inward or
walk away from

03:04.551 --> 03:07.254 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
any of our partners in the
world.

03:07.287 --> 03:12.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Faced with challenges like
migration, they
demanded a politics that is more
in touch

03:12.192 --> 03:17.164 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with their concerns and bold
action to address
them.

03:17.197 --> 03:20.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But that action must be more
global, not less.

03:20.067 --> 03:23.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But for many
leaders, Syria
topped the agenda.

03:24.004 --> 03:29.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama aimed strong
criticism at
the Syrians' main ally, Russia,
for its aggressive

03:30.010 --> 03:31.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
moves there and in Ukraine.

03:31.878 --> 03:38.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: In a world that
left the age
of empire behind, we see Russia
attempting

03:38.685 --> 03:41.388 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to recover lost glory through
force.

03:41.421 --> 03:47.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It may fuel nationalist fervor
for a time,
but, over time, it's also going
to diminish

03:47.060 --> 03:49.896 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
its stature and make its borders
less secure.

03:49.930 --> 03:56.837 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: U.N.
Secretary-General Ban
Ki-Moon also forcefully
denounced the Syrian

03:56.870 --> 04:01.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
regime, and its main backer, in
his last address
to the General Assembly.

04:01.374 --> 04:04.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BAN KI-MOON, United Nations
Secretary-General:
There is no military solution.

04:04.544 --> 04:12.018 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many groups have killed many
innocents, none
more so than the government of
Syria, which

04:12.052 --> 04:18.024 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
continues to bomb neighborhoods
and systematically
torture thousands of detainees.

04:18.058 --> 04:23.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Powerful patrons also have blood
on their
hands.

04:23.663 --> 04:29.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: French President
Francois Hollande
added his own demand to stop the
killing in

04:29.903 --> 04:31.705 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Syria.

04:31.738 --> 04:35.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRANCOIS HOLLANDE, French
President (through
translator): The Syrian tragedy
will be seen

04:35.308 --> 04:40.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by history as a disgrace for the
international
community if we do not end it
quickly.

04:41.014 --> 04:42.949 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Thousands of children have died
in bombings.

04:42.983 --> 04:45.652 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Whole populations are starving.

04:45.685 --> 04:47.354 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Humanitarian convoys are being
attacked.

04:47.387 --> 04:49.322 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Chemical weapons are being used.

04:49.356 --> 04:54.895 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Turkey's
President Recep Tayyip
Erdogan joined those who called
for a solution

04:54.928 --> 05:02.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Syria, but his main focus was
an exiled
cleric in the U.S., Fethullah
Gulen, whom

05:02.102 --> 05:06.406 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Erdogan and his government
accuse of fomenting
the failed July coup.

05:06.439 --> 05:12.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN, Turkish
President (through
translator): I am calling, from
this podium,

05:12.879 --> 05:17.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to all of our friends to swiftly
take the
necessary measures against the
Gulenist terrorist

05:17.584 --> 05:21.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
organization for their own
safety and the
future of their nations.

05:21.488 --> 05:25.325 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The General
Assembly continues
through next Monday.

05:25.358 --> 05:31.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In the day's other
news: New details
emerged on Ahmad Khan Rahami,
the suspect

05:31.598 --> 05:33.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the New York and New Jersey
bombings.

05:33.833 --> 05:40.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reported the
FBI briefly
investigated Rahami in 2014,
after he allegedly

05:40.473 --> 05:42.309 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
stabbed his brother.

05:42.342 --> 05:46.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the time, his father told
police that Rahami
was a -- quote -- "terrorist,"
but he later

05:46.780 --> 05:49.349 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
recanted, and an investigation
found nothing.

05:49.382 --> 05:54.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Authorities in
France have
made eight new arrests in a
deadly truck attack

05:54.154 --> 06:00.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in July; 86 people were killed
when a driver
plowed through crowds of
revelers in the Mediterranean

06:00.760 --> 06:04.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
city of Nice on Bastille Day,
the French national
holiday.

06:04.898 --> 06:07.901 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The attacker, a Tunisian, was
killed by police.

06:07.934 --> 06:11.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The suspects arrested on Monday
are French
and Tunisian.

06:11.238 --> 06:17.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The United Nations
has suspended
all aid deliveries to Syria
after an attack

06:17.110 --> 06:20.580 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on a Red Crescent convoy killed
at least 20
people.

06:20.614 --> 06:25.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It happened near the northern
city of Aleppo,
just hours after a cease-fire
expired.

06:26.019 --> 06:30.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Footage today showed the charred
wreckage
of trucks lining the streets,
and supplies,

06:30.523 --> 06:33.193 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some marked with the U.N. logo,
strewn about.

06:33.226 --> 06:35.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENS LAERKE, U.N. Office for the
Coordination
of Humanitarian Affairs: This is
a very, very

06:35.428 --> 06:41.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
dark day for humanitarians in
Syria, and I
will say across the world,
because I think

06:41.968 --> 06:52.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there's been a moment of shock
and, frankly,
disgust by this attack.

06:52.879 --> 06:58.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Russia denied claims
that its
warplanes attacked the convoy.

06:58.518 --> 07:03.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it did say there is drone
footage showing
heavily armed militants
traveling with the

07:03.390 --> 07:05.292 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
aid trucks.

07:05.325 --> 07:09.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A fire roared
through a migrant
camp on the Greek island of
Lesbos overnight.

07:09.963 --> 07:14.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Thousands fled and no one was
injured, but
60 percent of the camp was
destroyed.

07:14.401 --> 07:18.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The fire broke out late Monday
and was extinguished
by midday today.

07:18.772 --> 07:21.975 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The camp houses several thousand
migrants.

07:22.008 --> 07:25.745 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Police say the fire started
after clashes
between different ethnic groups.

07:25.779 --> 07:29.516 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Back in this
country, Hillary
Clinton took a day off the trail
to study

07:29.549 --> 07:34.921 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
up for next week's first
presidential debate,
while Donald Trump went back to
school.

07:34.954 --> 07:36.956 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John Yang has our report.

07:36.990 --> 07:41.995 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Donald Trump went to
college today,
courting the millennial vote.

07:42.028 --> 07:47.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At High Point University in
North Carolina,
he appeared to lecture Hillary
Clinton about

07:47.100 --> 07:48.868 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
fighting terrorism.

07:48.902 --> 07:51.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
Her claim that my opposition to
radical Islamic

07:52.005 --> 07:54.341 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
terrorism is a recruiting tool.

07:54.374 --> 07:55.709 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
But why?

07:55.742 --> 07:58.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Because I'm tough, it's a
recruiting tool?

07:58.445 --> 08:02.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It demonstrates a level of
ignorance about
the terror threat.

08:02.182 --> 08:07.020 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: It came amid more
questions about
the charitable Trump Foundation.

08:07.053 --> 08:12.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Washington Post reported it
paid more
than $250,000 to settle lawsuits
involving

08:12.759 --> 08:14.127 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
his businesses.

08:14.160 --> 08:17.097 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Trump campaign didn't
respond.

08:17.130 --> 08:23.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And social media became a
battleground over
Donald Trump Jr.'s tweet
likening Syrian refugees

08:23.370 --> 08:25.839 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to a tainted bowl of Skittles.

08:25.872 --> 08:31.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A Clinton campaign spokesman
called it disgusting,
and a former Obama speechwriter
tweeted a

08:31.678 --> 08:37.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
picture that had earlier gone
viral, saying,
this Syrian boy is "one of the
millions of

08:37.550 --> 08:41.087 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
children you compared to a
poisoned Skittle."

08:41.121 --> 08:45.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Clinton made no public
appearances today,
but there was word she may get
the vote of

08:45.492 --> 08:48.128 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a former Republican president.

08:48.161 --> 08:52.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Politico reported that former
Maryland Republican
Lieutenant Governor Kathleen
Kennedy Townsend,

08:52.799 --> 08:58.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
daughter of the late Robert
Kennedy, posted
on Facebook that George H.W.
Bush had told

08:58.138 --> 09:00.140 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
her he's voting for Hillary.

09:00.173 --> 09:06.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, a Bush spokesman said the
former president
is a private citizen and his
vote will be,

09:06.146 --> 09:07.847 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
too, private.

09:07.881 --> 09:10.316 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang.

09:10.350 --> 09:16.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Relief is on the
way for five
Southern states after a gasoline
pipeline

09:16.089 --> 09:17.924 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
leak in Alabama.

09:17.957 --> 09:23.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Colonial Pipeline said today
that it's completed
a bypass line, and it can
restart the flow

09:23.696 --> 09:25.131 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tomorrow.

09:25.165 --> 09:28.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The leak has caused many gas
stations in the
region to shut down pumps.

09:28.735 --> 09:32.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And prices have jumped more than
20 cents
in some parts.

09:32.172 --> 09:37.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Twenty-one states
went to federal
court today to block a new
overtime pay rule.

09:37.210 --> 09:44.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It takes effect December 1 and
requires overtime
for salaried workers making less
than $47,500.

09:45.018 --> 09:46.953 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's double the current
threshold.

09:46.986 --> 09:50.623 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The states say it places a heavy
new burden
on state budgets.

09:50.657 --> 09:53.026 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And a slow day on
Wall Street.

09:53.059 --> 09:58.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained nine
points to close near 18130.

09:58.665 --> 10:03.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose six, and the S&amp;P
500 added
a fraction.

10:03.470 --> 10:08.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
new details
on abuse at a Marine training
camp; Tulsa

10:08.775 --> 10:15.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
police promise justice after the
death of
an unarmed black man; breaking
down the presidential

10:15.081 --> 10:21.821 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
candidates' plans on education;
and much more.

10:21.855 --> 10:35.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The CEO of Wells
Fargo appeared
on Capitol Hill and faced a
barrage of questions

10:35.735 --> 10:41.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about the bank's conduct under
his leadership,
and why employees opened nearly
two million

10:41.341 --> 10:43.243 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
phony accounts.

10:43.276 --> 10:48.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Regulators say employees, under
pressure to
meet sales goals, had secretly
created unauthorized

10:48.248 --> 10:54.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
bank and credit card accounts
for customers,
since 2011, without their
knowledge.

10:54.087 --> 10:58.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, bank chairman John Stumpf
apologized
before the Senate Banking
Committee.

10:59.025 --> 11:04.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN STUMPF, CEO, Wells Fargo &amp;
Company: I
am deeply sorry that we failed
to fulfill

11:04.163 --> 11:10.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on our responsibility to our
customers, to
our team members and to the
American public.

11:10.870 --> 11:17.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We never directed, nor wanted
our team members
to provide products and services
to customers

11:17.577 --> 11:20.013 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
