subject to possible further
sanction for their

20:50.282 --> 20:52.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
actions in these cases.

20:52.084 --> 20:55.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You and I were
also discussing
the fact that, over years, there
have been

20:55.855 --> 21:00.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
allegations made about what's
been going on
at Parris Island.

21:00.826 --> 21:07.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Have they changed their
techniques, the M.O.,
the way they operate in general
over time?

21:07.199 --> 21:11.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The Marine
Corps would say,
yes, that they have been very
diligent about

21:11.237 --> 21:13.005 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
this.

21:13.038 --> 21:15.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was a notorious incident
back in the
'50s where a drill instructor
led a group

21:15.474 --> 21:19.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of recruits into a very
dangerous circumstance
and several died.

21:19.345 --> 21:21.247 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Reforms were made after that.

21:21.280 --> 21:24.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were also a series of
reforms and training
made after the end of the
Vietnam era, when

21:24.450 --> 21:28.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we moved from a draft to a more
volunteer
army.

21:28.087 --> 21:33.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With regards to these particular
allegations,
the biggest concern that we
heard in talking

21:33.225 --> 21:39.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to current Marines and former
Marines is that
the leadership failed in their
job here, that

21:39.965 --> 21:45.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this type of abuse shouldn't
have been allowed
to fester and blossom the way it
did.

21:45.337 --> 21:49.108 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's really the most
damning part of
the investigation, is that the
supervisory

21:49.141 --> 21:54.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
officers who should have been
observing this
activity really were absent and
negligent

21:54.813 --> 21:55.814 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of their duties.

21:55.848 --> 21:57.816 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It is such a
disturbing story.

21:57.850 --> 22:01.520 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I know the reporting on it
continues,
as well as the investigation.

22:01.554 --> 22:04.356 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
William Brangham, thank you.

22:04.390 --> 22:12.364 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Thank you.

22:12.398 --> 22:20.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: There are new calls
for a federal
investigation into the police
shooting of

22:20.673 --> 22:26.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
an unarmed black man in Tulsa,
Oklahoma, raising
questions yet again about the
relationship

22:26.679 --> 22:29.982 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
between law enforcement and
citizens of color.

22:30.015 --> 22:34.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Forty-year-old Terence Crutcher
was killed
on Friday when local officers
responded to

22:34.753 --> 22:38.524 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a call of a stalled vehicle in
the middle
of the road.

22:38.557 --> 22:43.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Police video subsequently showed
Crutcher,
hands in the air, walking away
from the officers

22:43.862 --> 22:46.198 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
before police fired.

22:46.232 --> 22:47.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Here is some of that video.

22:47.833 --> 22:52.671 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: That looks like a bad dude,
too.

22:52.705 --> 22:57.076 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: I think he may have just
been Tasered.

22:57.109 --> 22:58.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Shots fired!

22:58.377 --> 23:00.479 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: We have shots fired.

23:00.512 --> 23:02.648 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have one suspect down.

23:02.681 --> 23:07.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: An attorney for the
officer said
she believed Crutcher was armed
and didn't

23:07.620 --> 23:09.421 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
heed instruction.

23:09.455 --> 23:14.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But attorneys for the family say
the video
proves otherwise, and they
believe the officer

23:14.059 --> 23:17.863 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who shot him, Betty Jo Shelby,
should be charged
with murder.

23:17.896 --> 23:20.132 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She is on paid administrative
leave.

23:20.165 --> 23:25.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His twin sister, Tiffany, noted
that officers
watching at a distance from a
helicopter could

23:25.804 --> 23:29.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be heard on tape referring to
her brother
as a "bad dude."

23:29.842 --> 23:35.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIFFANY CRUTCHER, Sister of
Terence Crutcher:
That big, bad dude was my twin
brother.

23:35.281 --> 23:41.287 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That big, bad dude was a father.

23:41.320 --> 23:44.957 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That big, bad dude was a son.

23:44.990 --> 23:52.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That big, bad dude was enrolled
at Tulsa Community
College, just wanting to make us
proud.

23:52.298 --> 23:57.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: For the latest on
the investigation
and the mood in the city of
Tulsa, I am joined

23:57.870 --> 24:01.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by Ginnie Graham, columnist for
the Tulsa
World Newspaper.

24:01.106 --> 24:06.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ginnie Graham, The Washington
Post keeps a
database now in which they say,
in the past

24:06.679 --> 24:14.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
year, 696 people, 172 of them
black men, have
been fatally shot by police.

24:14.086 --> 24:16.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In Tulsa, how did this come
about?

24:16.522 --> 24:21.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GINNIE GRAHAM, Tulsa World: This
particular
incident, some of that is
unfolding.

24:21.393 --> 24:26.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that he had a stalled
car and that
the officer, Betty Shelby, was
responding

24:26.665 --> 24:29.868 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to a different call and came
upon him.

24:29.902 --> 24:35.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem is, there is some
missing video
-- or not missing video -- there
was no video

24:35.074 --> 24:38.644 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
leading up to what we now see.

24:38.677 --> 24:41.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's pretty clear that he
had his hands
up.

24:41.780 --> 24:44.249 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And you can see other officers
responded.

24:44.283 --> 24:47.052 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Then you had the aerial view.

24:47.086 --> 24:48.053 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And he was shot.

24:48.087 --> 24:49.988 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He was Tasered and then shot.

24:50.022 --> 24:54.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so people are coming to
their own conclusions
watching the video, and other
people have

24:54.727 --> 25:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lingering questions about what
led up to that,
how he responded, and then how
the officers

25:00.866 --> 25:04.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
responded directly after that,
because he
was left on the street.

25:04.636 --> 25:05.604 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: Yes.

25:05.637 --> 25:07.473 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He was left on the street for
some time.

25:07.506 --> 25:10.709 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Was there -- is there a
distinction or a dispute
between what the police account
of the incident

25:10.743 --> 25:12.711 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is and what others are saying?

25:12.745 --> 25:15.247 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GINNIE GRAHAM: Not so much right
now.

25:15.280 --> 25:17.850 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The police aren't saying too
much.

25:17.883 --> 25:20.986 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are launching their own
investigation.

25:21.019 --> 25:25.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they will be returning those
results over
to the district attorney, who
will decide

25:25.224 --> 25:26.358 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on a charge.

25:26.392 --> 25:29.128 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there is also another
investigation going
on.

25:29.161 --> 25:35.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The police chief had called the
Justice Department
early on, and the U.S. attorney
is looking

25:35.267 --> 25:40.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
into this as an independent and
parallel investigation
to see if there are any federal
civil rights

25:40.272 --> 25:41.573 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
violations that occurred.

25:41.607 --> 25:45.377 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so he will be releasing
those results
at the same time.

25:45.411 --> 25:50.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: We got to see this
video relatively
quickly, more quickly than we
often see in

25:50.449 --> 25:52.217 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
these cases.

25:52.251 --> 25:56.054 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Do you think what happened in
Tulsa with the
police rapid response, or
relatively rapid

25:56.088 --> 25:59.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
response, is the result of what
we have seen
happen in other cities and other
places?

25:59.825 --> 26:02.728 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GINNIE GRAHAM: It could be.

26:02.761 --> 26:07.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
There are also efforts
throughout the year
to talk about race in Tulsa.

26:07.199 --> 26:12.704 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have had a dubious history of
dealing with
race issues.

26:12.738 --> 26:18.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so for the last decade or
two decades,
there have been various groups
to try to forge

26:18.677 --> 26:22.080 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
relationships in between these
tense times.

26:22.114 --> 26:26.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so this is going to be a
challenge for
the city's leaders on how they
move forward.

26:26.718 --> 26:31.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think the other cities and
how they
have dealt with that are
certainly a caution.

26:31.623 --> 26:36.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's also a call for
transparency to
get the information out quickly,
put it out

26:36.995 --> 26:43.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the public, and then we can
make decisions
from there on what -- if they
acted correctly.

26:43.669 --> 26:48.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: When you talk about
Tulsa's dubious
history, you're referring not
only to instances

26:48.574 --> 26:53.345 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
where there have been
police-involved shootings,
but going all the way back to
1921, right?

26:53.378 --> 26:55.113 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GINNIE GRAHAM: Exactly.

26:55.147 --> 27:01.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We had an infamous 1921 race
riot, and it
burned a section of the city to
the ground.

27:01.153 --> 27:04.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it was the part of the city
referred to
as Black Wall Street.

27:04.556 --> 27:09.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And for decades, that wound was
left to fester.

27:09.228 --> 27:11.196 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That part of town was never
rebuilt.

27:11.230 --> 27:15.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The families were never given
any sort of
help to rebuild.

27:15.634 --> 27:20.606 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it was only in the 1990s
that a commission
was established to investigate
what happened

27:20.639 --> 27:22.541 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
during that time.

27:22.574 --> 27:28.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And since then, there is the
John Hope Reconciliation
Center that holds a national
forum on race.

27:28.080 --> 27:34.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are other groups in the
city that hold
seminars, symposiums, dialogues
and talks.

27:35.020 --> 27:40.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But all of that is going to be
tested right
now, as I said, because, right
now, people

27:40.893 --> 27:41.860 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are upset.

27:41.894 --> 27:42.861 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They're grieving.

27:42.895 --> 27:44.696 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They're angry.

27:44.730 --> 27:47.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so how the city responds,
whether they're
going to be straightforward,
whether they're

27:47.833 --> 27:53.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
going to live up to their
promises, that's
what's going to determine the
relationships

27:53.939 --> 27:55.774 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from here on out.

27:55.807 --> 28:03.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, hopefully, our city has
learned some lessons
on how to heal, how to deal with
this in a

28:03.081 --> 28:05.751 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
peaceful, yet justful manner.

28:05.784 --> 28:13.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, and it should
be said that,
right up until now, we haven't
seen riots

28:13.125 --> 28:17.596 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or unrest or fires or looting,
have we?

28:17.629 --> 28:20.132 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GINNIE GRAHAM: Not in Tulsa.

28:20.165 --> 28:26.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And we have had a couple
incidents before
where, last year, we had our
county deputy

28:26.939 --> 28:32.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sheriff, a reserve officer, shot
and killed
an unarmed black man as well.

28:32.244 --> 28:37.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And our district attorney filed
charges in
that with a secondary
manslaughter conviction.

28:37.783 --> 28:43.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there is some history that
our city leaders
will do the right thing.

28:43.722 --> 28:49.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there have been calls from
the family
and from other leaders to be
patient, but

28:49.127 --> 28:57.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
yet, you know, keep up the
oversight, because
protests are more than welcome.

28:57.502 --> 29:02.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our city -- our police chief
even said he
invites protesters.

29:02.407 --> 29:04.176 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They came into the press
conference.

29:04.209 --> 29:08.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The hope is that they can remain
peaceful
and that we can sit down and
have this discussion

29:08.680 --> 29:13.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about, you know, how can we be
safe on our
streets and how can we build
trust that people

29:13.418 --> 29:17.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that are living in North Tulsa
and all over
Tulsa feel safe with the police
that are on

29:17.990 --> 29:21.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the streets and find out what
happened and
to act swiftly.

29:21.660 --> 29:25.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Ginnie Graham,
columnist for the
Tulsa World, thank you very
much.

29:25.430 --> 29:30.168 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GINNIE GRAHAM: Thank you.

29:30.202 --> 29:39.044 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

29:39.077 --> 29:44.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": Ken
Burns' newest
film about a couple who dared to
defy the

29:44.683 --> 29:50.188 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nazis; and the overlooked
challenges of first-generation
college students.

29:50.222 --> 29:55.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, our coverage of the
issues in
this presidential campaign
continues.

29:55.527 --> 29:59.631 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we're taking the opportunity
to focus
on where they stand on
education, as part

29:59.665 --> 30:02.501 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of our weekly series Making the
Grade.

30:02.534 --> 30:06.071 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Correspondent Lisa Desjardins
gets us started
with this primer.

30:06.104 --> 30:09.975 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It is a wide
education gap.

30:10.008 --> 30:16.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The candidates disagree not just
on how to
fix schools, but also on what
the problems

30:16.248 --> 30:17.215 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
are.

30:17.249 --> 30:18.950 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
First, Donald Trump.

30:18.984 --> 30:20.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
That's why I'm proposing a plan
to provide

30:20.252 --> 30:23.588 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
school choice to every
disadvantaged student
in America.

30:23.622 --> 30:29.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The Republican
wants a $12,000
voucher for every child living
in poverty.

30:29.127 --> 30:35.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: That means parents
will be able
to send their kids to the
desired public,

30:35.100 --> 30:38.303 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
private, or even religious
school of their
choice.

30:38.336 --> 30:47.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Here's Trump's
math; $12,000
times 11 million kids, that's
over $130 billion.

30:47.212 --> 30:52.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To pay for that, Trump would
kick in $20 billion
in federal funds, and he'd like
states to

30:52.551 --> 30:57.089 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
find the rest, over $100
billion.

30:57.122 --> 31:02.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Libertarian Gary Johnson has
long pushed for
vouchers, but he is to the right
of Trump

31:02.327 --> 31:03.929 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on something else.

31:03.962 --> 31:09.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He would close the Department of
Education
and send savings back to the
states.

31:09.301 --> 31:14.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hillary Clinton, on the other
hand, strongly
opposes vouchers, charging that
Trump's plan

31:14.172 --> 31:16.742 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
would gut public school funding.

31:16.775 --> 31:22.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of her biggest changes would
be for even
younger kids, a universal
preschool plan that

31:22.347 --> 31:24.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was part of her campaign launch
last year.

31:24.716 --> 31:29.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate:
Our country won't be competitive
or fair if

31:29.454 --> 31:34.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we don't help more families give
their kids
the best possible start in life.

31:34.726 --> 31:39.331 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Another
contrast, the Common
Core education standards.

31:39.364 --> 31:41.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
